      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAXI GRIN (6) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish second, beaten 2.5 lengths (29.75) at this track in a Free For All over 515m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Can measure up this time. LORRAINE JACKY (8) had been in super honest form hitting the frame two times on end before finishing fourth (25.79) at Ballarat last time. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Bold showing expected. OKLAHOMA BALE (3) has shown good improvement at his last two starts, most recently finishing 3rd at this track over 515m. Will give a great sight again. LADY TSUNADE (1) recorded a 2.75 lengths win (23.12) in a Grade 6 last time at Mt Gambier. Has already won two times from this draw.",
